      <description>Would you agree that clerics should be able to do more damage moment to moment in a combat?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It is fairly clear that clerics despite plate armor are not intended to survive more than 5 seconds against the average of high end content.  It is also clear that if we get agro we are meant to die, which causes most of the group to die for a sudden drop in healing capacity.  The greatest issue clerics have at this time is not to be able to finish fights that for what ever reason we are a party to.  Usually because it found us, it summons, and it isn't going to forget we were there.  Still is there any good reason that since our roots do not stick to creatures and force them to fight us toe to toe; that we cannot do enough damage to kill a creature that is running away?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Or more credibly to be a viable part of a group as something besides a healer.  With the average dps of all other classes between 300 and 500 (some are far more), we too should be capable of doing at least 300 dps.  Or we should be able to aid our group in achieving 500 more dps than if we were not present.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Its really very simple.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Chisaineko of the Vazaelle</description>
