    <item>
      <title>Re: Damage ..</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=9017#M9017</link>
      <description>&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Morvain wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cleric nukes are the same as chanter nukes arent they?&amp;nbsp; So right now in most group setting you should be able to generate the same dps as a chanter nuking.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Depends on how you look at it.&amp;nbsp; --(and looking solely at base damage since foci and aa can tip scales in either direction)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ancient lev 70 nuke wise, Ancient Neurosis (enc) costs 398 mana for 1634 hp decrease; Ancient pious Conscien. (cle) costs 457 mana for 1646 hp decrease.&amp;nbsp; So fairly close, cleric nuke costs 59 more mana and does 9 more damage.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Don (non ancient) nuke wise, Psycosis (enc) costs 375 mana for 1513 hp decrease; Reproach (cle) costs 430 mana for 1424 hp decrease.&amp;nbsp; So for these nuke equivelents, the enchanter nuke now costs 55 mana less and does 89 more damage.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So against non-undead mobs using top non ancient nukes, enchanters do more damage for less mana cost per nuke.&amp;nbsp; Additionally add in the very important magic debuffing, they by far will outdamage a cleric against live mobs using solely nukes.&amp;nbsp; For purpose of just comparing nukes, will leave out comparing pets, cle reverse ds, wards, haste, etc.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Looking at undead, clerics have a slight advantage with desolate undead costing 310 mana and hitting for 1610 hps.&amp;nbsp; However, finding a constant or even semi populated area of undead mobs where people want to group at 70 is fairly rare.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
